@NODE LongRoad "The future ?"


 * The Future:
 =============


  After both, a few brief and some not so brief emails with various AmosAGA
 supporters, and reading the recent Amos mailing lists posted to Aminet,
 there now appears (to me at least) that there indeed is going to be a
 future for the further development of this idea into fully functioning
 product.
  

  This product is be known as 'AmosAGA pro' and unlike the series
 of simple AmosAGA example sources I've presently released, it will be
 a fully functional AGA game & demo development environment designed
 with for Amos programmers in mind.  AmosAGA pro, will not come in the form
 of an extension as such, but that of a highly optimized (pure assembly)
 Amiga shared library & Amos API.


  The use of an external library has many benefits over that of fixed
 extension, for example.



  * Users all be able to use special cpu opt'd versions of the
    AmosAGA pro library.


  * Allows for support of the coming PPC cpu's.  So Amos developers never
    need to worry about PPC issues.


  * An standard shared library (which is really just a collection of
    functions) can be used from any host environment or language, such as
    Blitz Basic, C, E, or even assembly.

    Initially though, we'll be focusing our support on the Amos / AmosPro
    community, as I believe they need this support the most.  ;)


  * Users and developers will benefit directly from official updates to
    the 'AmosAGA pro' user graphics library.



  
  Future:  (Coming in 1997)
  =======


  * Loading & Saving of AGA IFF's

  * AGA Open Screen      You'll be able to open and use a variety of screen
                         types, including.

			    * Normal Planar
                            * Interleaved Planar
                            * Chunky (8bit)
                            & possible Graffiti support.


  * A completely new copper control system.

  * Palette & colour  control.

  * Standard drawing functions, including  Plot, Line, box, Circle etc. etc.

  * A new BOB system(s).

  * Custom Map tile system(s).

  * Hardware Sprite Control.




 Techy AGA info:
 ===============


  * Support for AGA 16/32 & 64 bit burst modes

  * Extended Long Blits (ECS & AGA)




  Extended Future:  (coming in 1998)
  ================


  * 3D Library, including 256 colour Flat shaded, gouraud shaded, &
                texture mapped polygons.

  * 3D Object Editor,  Will import 'Imagine' & hopefully (grin) Amos3D
                objects.
 



  The graphics function library that AmosAGA pro will be based upon is
 being developed in pure 680x0 assembly for maximum speed and uses the very
 lastest in software technologies to achieve superior performance.


  If you have any possible feature ideas please feel free to forward
 them to me.




@ENDNODE




